summary: The document is an identification form detailing an agent's report on Manuel Marti, a former employee of the Mutual Insurance Advisory Association, investigated in connection with DOD-affiliated personnel incident investigations related to the JFK assassination system. It includes Marti's personal details, employment history, and the investigation's findings, which found no adverse information regarding Marti's employment or background. The document was classified as 'UNCLASSIFIED' but was released with deletions.
key_findings: Manuel Marti was investigated as part of DOD-affiliated personnel incident investigations.
Marti worked at the Mutual Insurance Advisory Association from April 5, 1965, to May 20, 1968, before entering military service.
The investigation found no adverse information regarding Marti's employment or background.
The document was classified as 'UNCLASSIFIED' but was released with deletions.
